class eczPhpGenerator eZPHPCreator provides a simple interface for creating and executing PHP code.  To create PHP code you must create an instance of this class, add any number of elements you choose with addDefine(), addVariable(), addVariableUnset(), addVariableUnsetList(), addSpace(), addText(), addMethodCall(), addCodePiece(), addComment() and addInclude(). After that you call store() to write all changes to disk. 
<code> $php = new eZPHPCreator( 'cache', 'code.php' );  $php->addComment( 'Auto generated' ); $php->addInclude( 'inc.php' ); $php->addVariable( 'count', 10 );  $php->store();
</code>
